<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="186" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,159,2091]" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,856,1131,1155]" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">
Morphological evidence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harley" authorityYear="1992" box="[494,644,1131,1155]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="piranii">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[494,644,1131,1155]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Hyptis piranii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
generic position—
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harley" authorityYear="1992" box="[856,1004,1132,1155]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="piranii">
<emphasis box="[856,1004,1132,1155]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Hyptis piranii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Harley, R. M." box="[1197,1348,1131,1155]" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" pagination="553 - 580" refId="ref3014" refString="Harley, R. M. (1992) New Taxa of Labiatae from the Pico das Almas and the Chapada Diamantina. Kew Bulletin 47: 553 - 580. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 4110695" type="journal article" year="1992">Harley (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, based on the material collected by Pirani 
<emphasis box="[470,516,1167,1191]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">et al</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[537,677,1167,1191]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">CFCR 13069</emphasis>
) in the southern portion of Espinhaço Range, 
<collectingRegion box="[1160,1360,1167,1191]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Minas Gerais state</collectingRegion>
. Due the tomentose indumentum, composed of short and appressed white hairs, giving a silvery tonality, and the inflorescence born in the axil of leaf-like bracts, at first sight, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harley" authorityYear="1992" box="[591,697,1240,1263]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="piranii">
<emphasis box="[591,697,1240,1263]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">H. piranii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles two other species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Harley 1985: 614) Harley &amp; Pastore (2012: 33)" authorityName="Harley &amp; Pastore" authorityPageNumber="33" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Harley" baseAuthorityPageNumber="614" baseAuthorityYear="1985" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Stylocephalidae" genus="Oocephalus" kingdom="Chromista" order="Eugregarinida" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Miozoa" rank="species" species="argyrophyllus">
<emphasis box="[1014,1296,1239,1263]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Oocephalus argyrophyllus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Harley, R. M." pageId="2" pageNumber="185" pagination="609 - 625" refId="ref2868" refString="Harley, R. M. (1985) New Taxa in Hyptis sect. Polydesmia Benth. from Bahia, Brazil: Notes on New World Labiatae: VI. Kew Bulletin 40: 609 - 625. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 4109621" type="journal article" year="1985">Harley 1985: 614</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Harley, R. M. &amp; Pastore, J. F. B." box="[193,503,1275,1299]" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref3164" refString="Harley, R. M. &amp; Pastore, J. F. B. (2012) A generic revision and new combinations in the Hyptidinae (Lamiaceae), based on molecular and morphological evidence. Phytotaxa 58: 1 - 55. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 58.1.1" type="journal article" year="2012">Harley &amp; Pastore (2012: 33)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(≡ 
<taxonomicName authority="Harley" authorityName="Harley" box="[543,796,1275,1299]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="argyrophylla">
<emphasis box="[543,714,1275,1299]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">H. argyrophylla</emphasis>
Harley
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Martius ex Bentham 1883: 94) Harley &amp; Pastore (2012: 34)" authorityName="Harley &amp; Pastore" authorityPageNumber="34" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Bentham" baseAuthorityPageNumber="94" baseAuthorityYear="1883" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Stylocephalidae" genus="Oocephalus" kingdom="Chromista" order="Eugregarinida" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Miozoa" rank="species" species="halimifolius">
<emphasis box="[859,1020,1275,1299]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">O. halimifolius</emphasis>
(Martius ex Bentham 1883: 94) 
<bibRefCitation author="Harley, R. M. &amp; Pastore, J. F. B." pageId="2" pageNumber="185" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref3164" refString="Harley, R. M. &amp; Pastore, J. F. B. (2012) A generic revision and new combinations in the Hyptidinae (Lamiaceae), based on molecular and morphological evidence. Phytotaxa 58: 1 - 55. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 58.1.1" type="journal article" year="2012">Harley &amp; Pastore (2012: 34)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(≡ 
<taxonomicName authority="Mart. ex Benth." authorityName="Benth." box="[406,740,1311,1335]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="halimifolia">
<emphasis box="[406,557,1311,1335]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">H. halimifolia</emphasis>
Mart. ex Benth.
</taxonomicName>
), both occurring in the Northern portion of the Espinhaço Range, 
<collectingRegion box="[136,256,1347,1371]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Bahia state</collectingRegion>
. These combined features led 
<bibRefCitation author="Harley, R. M." box="[572,722,1347,1371]" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" pagination="553 - 580" refId="ref3014" refString="Harley, R. M. (1992) New Taxa of Labiatae from the Pico das Almas and the Chapada Diamantina. Kew Bulletin 47: 553 - 580. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 4110695" type="journal article" year="1992">Harley (1992)</bibRefCitation>
to accommodate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harley" authorityYear="1992" box="[907,1011,1348,1371]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="piranii">
<emphasis box="[907,1011,1348,1371]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">H. piranii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[1097,1444,1347,1371]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Amorphothecaceae" genus="Polydesmia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Erysiphales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="subSection" subSection="Oocephalus">
<emphasis box="[1097,1221,1347,1371]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Polydesmia</emphasis>
subsect. 
<emphasis box="[1317,1444,1347,1371]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Oocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, along with five other species, including the two mentioned above. With the taxonomic combination proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Harley, R. M. &amp; Pastore, J. F. B." pageId="2" pageNumber="185" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref3164" refString="Harley, R. M. &amp; Pastore, J. F. B. (2012) A generic revision and new combinations in the Hyptidinae (Lamiaceae), based on molecular and morphological evidence. Phytotaxa 58: 1 - 55. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 58.1.1" type="journal article" year="2012">Harley &amp; Pastore (2012)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harley" authorityYear="1992" box="[309,416,1420,1443]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="piranii">
<emphasis box="[309,416,1420,1443]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">H. piranii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harley &amp; Pastore" authorityYear="2012" box="[580,707,1419,1443]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Stylocephalidae" genus="Oocephalus" kingdom="Chromista" order="Eugregarinida" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Miozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[580,707,1419,1443]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Oocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harley" authorityYear="1992" box="[752,859,1419,1443]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="piranii">
<emphasis box="[752,859,1419,1443]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">O. piranii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the inflorescence morphology, which is the main feature to distinguish 
<taxonomicName box="[436,555,1455,1479]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="187" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Hyptidinae">Hyptidinae</taxonomicName>
genera, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harley" authorityYear="1992" box="[680,787,1456,1479]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="piranii">
<emphasis box="[680,787,1456,1479]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">H. piranii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite different from the species belonging to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harley &amp; Pastore" authorityYear="2012" box="[1317,1444,1455,1479]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Stylocephalidae" genus="Oocephalus" kingdom="Chromista" order="Eugregarinida" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Miozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1317,1444,1455,1479]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Oocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. While 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harley &amp; Pastore" authorityYear="2012" box="[209,336,1491,1515]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Stylocephalidae" genus="Oocephalus" kingdom="Chromista" order="Eugregarinida" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Miozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[209,336,1491,1515]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Oocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
members have a thyrsoid structure composed of pedunculate or sessile, ± ovoid, bracteolate cluster of congested cyme and flowers with a long corolla tube and short lobes, these are never blotched or marked with any lines, 
<taxonomicName box="[136,289,1563,1587]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[136,206,1564,1587]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Hyptis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
are characterized by having cymose hemispherical capitula, or often spherical, with an involucre of a number of bracteoles, sometimes forming complex synflorescences, flowers usually small with posterior lobes often blotched or marked. Additionally, morphological analysis of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harley" authorityYear="1992" box="[655,760,1636,1659]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="piranii">
<emphasis box="[655,760,1636,1659]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">H. piranii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed the presence of a stylopodium (
<figureCitation box="[1193,1302,1635,1659]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,229,2019,2041]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,749,1992]" captionTargetId="figure-167@1.[201,1386,749,1992]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hyptis piranii: A: Three-flowered inflorescence; B: Detail of stylopodium overtopping the ovary; C: Inflorescence hidden in the axil of leaf-like bract on a flowering branch. Images:A and B taken from Zappi et al. CFCR 8542; C: Guilherme Antar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5912660" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5912660/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Figure 1B</figureCitation>
), which is the basal part of the style that persists jointed to the ovary apex after the fall of the distal portion, a feature absent in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Stylocephalidae" genus="Oocephalus" kingdom="Chromista" order="Eugregarinida" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Miozoa" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1324,1451,1671,1695]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Oocephalus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Harley, R. M." box="[226,362,1707,1731]" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" pagination="9539" refId="ref3055" refString="Harley, R. M. (2014) Four new taxa of Oocephalus (Hyptidinae: Lamiaceae) from Bahia, Brazil. Kew Bulletin 69: 9539. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12225 - 014 - 9539 - 4" type="journal article" year="2014">Harley 2014</bibRefCitation>
; Soares 
<emphasis box="[448,500,1707,1731]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">et al.</emphasis>
2021). This morphological character has an important role in the taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName box="[1326,1447,1707,1731]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="187" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Hyptidinae">Hyptidinae</taxonomicName>
, as pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation author="Harley, R. M." box="[333,487,1743,1767]" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" pagination="87 - 95" refId="ref2958" refString="Harley, R. M. (1988) Revision of generic limits in Hyptis Jacq. (Labiatae) and its allies. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Soci ety 98: 87 - 95. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8339.1988. tb 01697. x" type="journal article" year="1988">Harley (1988)</bibRefCitation>
, who used it as a diagnostic character for members of 
<taxonomicName authority="Humboldt &amp; Bonpland ex Bentham (1833: 142)" authorityName="Bentham" authorityPageNumber="142" authorityYear="1833" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Eriope" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1087,1160,1744,1767]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Eriope</emphasis>
Humboldt &amp; Bonpland ex 
<bibRefCitation author="Bentham, G." box="[136,370,1779,1803]" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" pagination="62 - 145" refId="ref2775" refString="Bentham, G. (1833) Labiatarum genera et species. Ridgeway &amp; Sons, London, pp. 62 - 145." type="book chapter" year="1833">Bentham (1833: 142)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Martius ex Bentham 1833: 136) Harley (1988: 91)" authorityName="Harley" authorityPageNumber="91" authorityYear="1988" baseAuthorityName="Bentham" baseAuthorityPageNumber="136" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[382,1042,1779,1803]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hypenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[382,472,1780,1803]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Hypenia</emphasis>
(Martius ex 
<bibRefCitation author="Bentham, G." box="[615,829,1779,1803]" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" pagination="62 - 145" refId="ref2775" refString="Bentham, G. (1833) Labiatarum genera et species. Ridgeway &amp; Sons, London, pp. 62 - 145." type="book chapter" year="1833">Bentham 1833: 136</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Harley, R. M." box="[845,1042,1779,1803]" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" pagination="87 - 95" refId="ref2958" refString="Harley, R. M. (1988) Revision of generic limits in Hyptis Jacq. (Labiatae) and its allies. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Soci ety 98: 87 - 95. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8339.1988. tb 01697. x" type="journal article" year="1988">Harley (1988: 91)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Harley (1986: 90)" authorityName="Harley" authorityPageNumber="90" authorityYear="1986" box="[1055,1405,1779,1803]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptidendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1055,1202,1779,1803]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Hyptidendron</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Harley, R. M." box="[1210,1405,1779,1803]" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" pagination="995 - 1005" refId="ref2917" refString="Harley, R. M. (1986) Notes on New world Labiatae IX. Hyptis sect. Pachyphyllae in Brazil. Kew Bulletin 41: 995 - 1005. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 4102997" type="journal article" year="1986">Harley (1986: 90)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and some sections of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacquin" authorityYear="1786" box="[320,390,1816,1839]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[320,390,1816,1839]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Hyptis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,159,2091]" lastBlockId="3.[136,1452,159,687]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="186" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,476,1851,1875]" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Sectional classification—</emphasis>
Of the currently recognized sections of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacquin" authorityYear="1786" box="[915,985,1852,1875]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[915,985,1852,1875]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Hyptis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sect. 
<emphasis box="[1058,1157,1851,1875]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Apodotes</emphasis>
Benth., sect. 
<emphasis box="[1311,1452,1851,1875]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Eriosphaeria</emphasis>
Benth., sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="Epling" authorityName="Epling" box="[276,463,1887,1911]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Induratae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[276,381,1887,1911]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Induratae</emphasis>
Epling
</taxonomicName>
, sect. 
<emphasis box="[529,674,1887,1911]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Pachyphyllae</emphasis>
Harley and sect. 
<emphasis box="[863,982,1887,1911]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Xylodontes</emphasis>
Benth. possess a stylopodium. Members of sect. 
<emphasis box="[191,290,1923,1947]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Apodotes</emphasis>
has its flowers arranged in a hemispherical capitula, which could be sessile and forming a spike, as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Bentham (1833: 79)" authorityName="Bentham" authorityPageNumber="79" authorityYear="1833" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nudicaulis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Hyptis nudicaulis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bentham, G." box="[255,473,1959,1983]" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" pagination="62 - 145" refId="ref2775" refString="Bentham, G. (1833) Labiatarum genera et species. Ridgeway &amp; Sons, London, pp. 62 - 145." type="book chapter" year="1833">Bentham (1833: 79)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, or pedunculate, and calyx with subulate or lanceolate lobes with a deep sinus between the two anterior ones. In sect. 
<emphasis box="[421,539,1995,2019]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Xylodontes</emphasis>
, the indumentum of the capitula is slightly hirsute, calyx lobes are also lanceolate or subulate, and the bracteoles are somewhat larger. Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harley" authorityYear="1992" box="[871,1023,2032,2055]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="piranii">
<emphasis box="[871,1023,2032,2055]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Hyptis piranii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not matches with neither of these two sections. In the most recent 
<taxonomicName box="[477,596,2067,2091]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="187" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Hyptidinae">Hyptidinae</taxonomicName>
phylogeny (
<bibRefCitation author="Pastore, J. F. B. &amp; Antar, G. M. &amp; Soares, A. S. &amp; Forest, F. &amp; Harley, R. M." box="[727,929,2067,2091]" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" pagination="1086 - 1094" refId="ref3528" refString="Pastore, J. F. B., Antar, G. M., Soares, A. S., Forest, F. &amp; Harley, R. M. (2021) A new and expanded phylogenetic analyses of Hyptidinae (Lamiaceae). Systematic Botany 46: 1086 - 1094. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364421 X 16370109698542" type="journal article" year="2021">
Pastore 
<emphasis box="[813,866,2067,2091]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
), molecular data supports that sect. 
<emphasis box="[1306,1451,2067,2091]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Pachyphyllae</emphasis>
should revert to subsectional rank along with sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[670,775,159,183]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Induratae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[670,775,159,183]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Induratae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within sect. 
<emphasis box="[909,1050,159,183]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Eriosphaeria</emphasis>
, where 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harley" authorityYear="1992" box="[1133,1238,160,183]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="piranii">
<emphasis box="[1133,1238,160,183]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">H. piranii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
apparently belongs, corroborated by the anatomical results shown by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rudall, P." box="[685,840,195,219]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" pagination="319 - 340" refId="ref3597" refString="Rudall, P. (1980) Leaf anatomy of subtribe Hyptidinae (Labiatae). Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 80: 319 - 340. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8339.1980. tb 01667. x" type="journal article" year="1980">Rudall (1980)</bibRefCitation>
, that suggest a close relationship between the first two groups.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,159,687]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">
Species from sect. 
<emphasis box="[403,544,267,291]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Eriosphaeria</emphasis>
are herbs, shrubs or subshrubs densely covered with long or short hairs, flowers usually arranged in a hemispherical, short pedunculate capitulum with an involucre of narrowly lanceolate bracteoles and the gynoecium with a well-developed stylopodium (
<bibRefCitation author="Harley, R. M." box="[648,786,339,363]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" pagination="995 - 1005" refId="ref2917" refString="Harley, R. M. (1986) Notes on New world Labiatae IX. Hyptis sect. Pachyphyllae in Brazil. Kew Bulletin 41: 995 - 1005. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 4102997" type="journal article" year="1986">Harley 1986</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Harley, R. M. &amp; Antar, G. M." box="[795,1024,339,363]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" pagination="32" refId="ref3221" refString="Harley, R. M. &amp; Antar, G. M. (2019) Hyptis pastorei, an unusual new species of Hyptis sect. Eriosphaeria (Lamiaceae: Hyptidinae) from the Chapada dos Veadeiros, Goias, Brazil. Kew Bulletin 74: 32. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12225 - 019 - 9825 - 2" type="journal article" year="2019">Harley &amp; Antar 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Although 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harley" authorityYear="1992" box="[1146,1250,340,363]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="piranii">
<emphasis box="[1146,1250,340,363]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">H. piranii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has characters that place it in sect. 
<emphasis box="[301,442,375,399]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Eriosphaeria</emphasis>
, it still unclear into which subsection it would be best accommodated this species, even though it shares some similar characters with the species of subsect. 
<emphasis box="[798,917,412,435]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Passerinae</emphasis>
, such as leaf indumentum slender and appressed, bracteoles oblong, densely covered with short hairs and usually smaller than the calyx (
<bibRefCitation author="Epling, C." box="[1107,1246,447,471]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" pagination="153 - 497" refId="ref2837" refString="Epling, C. (1949) Revision del genero Hyptis (Labiatae). Revista Museu de. La Plata, Seccion. Botanica 7: 153 - 497." type="journal article" year="1949">Epling 1949</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Harley, R. M. &amp; Pastore, J. F. B." pageId="3" pageNumber="186" pagination="59 - 63" refId="ref3102" refString="Harley, R. M. &amp; Pastore, J. F. B. (2010) Hyptis kramerioides (Lamiaceae), a new species from central Brazil with notes on subsect. Passerinae. Kew Bulletin 65: 59 - 63. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12225 - 010 - 9186 - 3" type="journal article" year="2010">Harley &amp; Pastore 2010</bibRefCitation>
). Despite this, the inflorescence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harley" authorityYear="1992" box="[573,679,484,507]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="piranii">
<emphasis box="[573,679,484,507]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">H. piranii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite different from those species of subsect. 
<emphasis box="[1201,1320,484,507]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Passerinae</emphasis>
[
<emphasis box="[1336,1374,484,507]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">e.g.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Briquet (1898: 230)" authorityName="Briquet" authorityPageNumber="230" authorityYear="1898" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gardneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Hyptis gardneri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Briquet, J." box="[236,450,519,543]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" pagination="102 - 251" refId="ref2799" refString="Briquet, J. (1898) Fragmenta monographiae Labiatarum V. Observations sur quelques labiees interessantes ou nouvelles principalment de l'Herbier Delessert. Annuaire du Conservatoire et Jardin Botaniques de Geneve 2: 102 - 251." type="journal article" year="1898">Briquet (1898: 230)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Harley &amp; Pastore (2010: 59)" authorityName="Harley &amp; Pastore" authorityPageNumber="59" authorityYear="2010" box="[505,1043,519,543]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kramerioides">
<emphasis box="[505,723,519,543]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Hyptis kramerioides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Harley, R. M. &amp; Pastore, J. F. B." box="[730,1043,519,543]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" pagination="59 - 63" refId="ref3102" refString="Harley, R. M. &amp; Pastore, J. F. B. (2010) Hyptis kramerioides (Lamiaceae), a new species from central Brazil with notes on subsect. Passerinae. Kew Bulletin 65: 59 - 63. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12225 - 010 - 9186 - 3" type="journal article" year="2010">Harley &amp; Pastore (2010: 59)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
], which have inflorescence composed of pedunculate or sessile, subspherical capitulum surrounded by an involucre of bracteoles. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harley" authorityYear="1992" box="[1150,1256,556,579]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="piranii">
<emphasis box="[1150,1256,556,579]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">H. piranii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the inflorescence anomalous, being reduced to three flowers, appressed dorsiventrally and hidden by the leaf-like bracts and bracteoles not forming an involucre. A phylogenetic approach focusing on 
<taxonomicName box="[776,1048,627,651]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hyptis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Eriosphaeria">
<emphasis box="[776,846,628,651]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Hyptis</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[907,1048,627,651]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Eriosphaeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is needed and could indicate the right position of this species within it.
</paragraph>
